def get_master_context() -> str:
    return (
        "PLATFORM CONTEXT\n"
        "SoapBox Cloud is an EHS (Environment, Health & Safety) management platform used by organisations "
        "to track, respond to, and prevent safety and compliance-related events. Descriptions generated by "
        "this system are read by EHS professionals and operations managers. Language should be direct and "
        "professional — as if written by a knowledgeable person summarising what happened, what risk exists, "
        "what action is being taken, or what was found.\n"
        "\n"
        "UNIVERSAL FIELD DEFINITIONS\n"
        "The following fields appear across multiple modules and carry consistent meaning throughout the platform.\n"
        "\n"
        "Severity: How serious the event, risk, finding, or obligation is in terms of potential harm or business "
        "impact. Values range from Informational or Low through Medium and High to Critical. Higher severity "
        "warrants more urgent and weighty language.\n"
        "\n"
        "Priority: How urgently action needs to be taken. Related to but distinct from severity — a low-severity "
        "item can carry high priority if it is time-sensitive or affects many people.\n"
        "\n"
        "Site: The physical facility or location where the event occurred or where the activity is based.\n"
        "\n"
        "Area / Work Zone: A sub-location within a site — such as a production floor, warehouse section, "
        "laboratory, loading bay, or office block.\n"
        "\n"
        "Department: The organisational unit responsible for or affected by the record.\n"
        "\n"
        "Category / Subcategory: Classification labels that group records by type of hazard, event, or obligation.\n"
        "\n"
        "Status: Where in the workflow a record currently sits — open, in progress, completed, escalated, closed, etc.\n"
        "\n"
        "Due Date: A deadline for resolution or action, signalling a time-bound obligation.\n"
        "\n"
        "Owner / Assigned To: The person accountable for managing or resolving the record.\n"
        "\n"
        "Evidence Type: The kind of supporting media attached — photograph, video, report, certificate, etc.\n"
        "\n"
        "Linked Incident ID: A traceable reference connecting a corrective action or related record to the "
        "originating incident."
    )
